text: USCGC Triton may refer to: * Triton was a 165-foot cutter which operated out of Coast Guard Base 15 at Biloxi, Mississippi during what was referred to at the time as "the Prohibition War"--with operations against alcohol smugglers during Prohibition in the United States. * , was a patrol boat commissioned in 1934 and served until 1967 ==See also== * * Category:United States Coast Guard ship names
